                  <decoDesc>
                    <summary>(in the style of the Ground Hornbill painter). Compare the first miniature with EMIP 118/Weiner 27, f. ii v(erso). The style of this artwork and the pose is very reminiscent of the ground hornbill painter’s work as seen in Bodleian MS. Aeth. e. 28, f. 1v (see Demeke and Delamarter, Plate 9, p. 148). The same can be said for the subsequent pages with geometric patterns around the text</summary>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#1v" facs="005"/><desc>Man standing with arms upraised</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#2r" facs="006"/><desc>Elaborate geometric patterns surround the text on this page</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#44r" facs="090"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#164r" facs="330"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1035HolyMan"/>, A gospel writer or Saint Paul surrounded by geometric patterns.</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d5">
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#4r #32v #35v #39r #45r #45v #55v" facs="010 067 073 080 092 093 113"/>, etc. (multiple full stops);
                      <locus target="#10r" facs="022"/> (a line of full stops above a line of alternating red and black dots);
                      <locus target="#163v" facs="329"/> (lines of full stops and alternating red and black dots).
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
